cs.NE, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.CV 

The paper proposes a machine learning approach using deep neural networks for predicting future channel activity in space and time, which is a typical problem in the field of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also deals with wireless communication and congestion control, which are relevant topics in information theory (cs.IT). The use of machine learning for predicting channel activity can also be considered as a topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper focuses on vehicular safety communication, which involves the coordination of multiple vehicles, making it a topic in control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposal via simulation, which involves image processing and computer vision techniques (cs.CV).
